  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_830326\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_2048051_830326\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481855\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_2048051_481855\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Mary Colter's Hopi House</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5504724\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/images/Hopi-House-Banner_2.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"A historic image of Hopi House on the left and a modern image of Hopi House on the right.\" src=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/images/Hopi-House-Banner_2.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_2048061\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_2048061\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<p><strong>The Hopi House</strong> (1905) is a large, multi-story building of stone masonry, shaped and built like a Hopi pueblo. When Mary Colter was commissioned in 1904 by the Fred Harvey Company to design an “Indian Arts Building” as the hospitality giant liked to call their souvenir shops, the talented and stubborn architect was eager to accept the challenge. She was one of just a few women in a male-dominated field, and “lady-like” wasn’t in her vocabulary. Neither were the words “traditional European influences.” Colter’s vision extended well beyond that. Inspired by the natural beauty of the Grand Canyon, she wanted to design something that appeared native, natural and timeless.<br/>\n<br/>\nHopi House, modeled after the 1,000 year-old pueblo dwellings of the Hopi village in Old Oraibi, was a radically new experience for tourists. Colter’s attention to detail and human history created a strange and exotic world they could easily and safely enjoy.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6273853\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6273853\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/images/Hopi-House-Interior.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"A black and white photo of a sales room with baskets and Navajo rugs.\" src=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/images/Hopi-House-Interior.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"Hopi House Interior\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Hopi House Interior. Circa 1905. </figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<p>The Hopi House is rectangular in plan, and the multiple roofs are stepped at various levels giving the building the impression of pueblo architecture. The sandstone walls are reddish in color, and tiny windows, like those of true Hopi structures, allow only the smallest amount of light into the building and keep the hot desert sun from entering.<br/>\n<br/>\nInside, Mary Colter’s perfectionist tendencies are apparent even today. Most of the rooms have the typical ceiling of the Hopi style: saplings, grasses, and twigs with a mud coating on top, resting on peeled log beams. Corner fireplaces with chimneys are made from broken pottery jars stacked and mortared together. Baskets hang from peeled log beams and low ceilings thatched with young saplings. Pottery and jewelry are arranged for inspection on counters draped in hand-woven Navajo blankets and rugs.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe only concession Mary Colter made to the realities of the building’s modern day use is that, unlike traditional Hopi homes, there is no roof entrance. Instead Hopi House was given a front door so tourists could easily access and purchase the beautiful Native American arts and crafts to show to the folks back home.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5504788\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5504788\">\n<div class=\"Component FeatureGrid\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -medium\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/grand_canyon_nps/sets/72157626982621103/with/5898212348/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'https://www.flickr.com/photos/grand_canyon_nps/sets/72157626982621103/with/5898212348/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"Photo of Hopi House\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 640px, (min-width: 1200px) 550px, (min-width: 576px) 50vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/744DA066-1DD8-B71B-0B374E656FA3C686.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/744DA066-1DD8-B71B-0B374E656FA3C686.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/744DA066-1DD8-B71B-0B374E656FA3C686.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Hopi House (1905)</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Continue to the Hopi House photo gallery on Flickr.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -medium\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/hopi-house/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/hopi-house/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"The outside of the Hopi House\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 640px, (min-width: 1200px) 550px, (min-width: 576px) 50vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/23886B35-CFFD-FCC7-BB8C35BE8BC4C60C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/23886B35-CFFD-FCC7-BB8C35BE8BC4C60C.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/23886B35-CFFD-FCC7-BB8C35BE8BC4C60C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Hopi House History Continued</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Learn more about the Hopi House on Arizona State University's Nature, Culture, and History at Grand Canyon website.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/historic-village.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/historyculture/historic-village.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"The side of the Grand Canyon in the snow.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/594BFA1F-D914-9667-56FF83C36A125878.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/594BFA1F-D914-9667-56FF83C36A125878.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/594BFA1F-D914-9667-56FF83C36A125878.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">The Historic Village</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">With the arrival of the First Steam-Powered Train in 1901, the quiet area of the South Rim rapidly expanded into the Grand Canyon Village.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_index.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_index.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A black and white photo of a women sitting in a chair.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/58F5DD3C-C0A4-2B97-0170156EBE20185C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/58F5DD3C-C0A4-2B97-0170156EBE20185C.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/58F5DD3C-C0A4-2B97-0170156EBE20185C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Mary Colter's Buildings</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Mary Colter was the chief architect and decorator for the Fred Harvey Company from 1902 to 1948.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/entrepeneurs.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/historyculture/entrepeneurs.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"John Verkamp in front of his tent.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/214B190F-0E07-4A2C-2BD4BE784547DC36.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/214B190F-0E07-4A2C-2BD4BE784547DC36.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/214B190F-0E07-4A2C-2BD4BE784547DC36.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Entrepreneurs</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">After the Santa Fe Railroad started bringing visitors to the canyon, entrepreneurs came to the canyon to make their fortune.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: May 3, 2021</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
